The paper deals with the construction of a pseudorandom generator, which is a fundamental topic in theoretical computer science and cryptography. The lower bound result is related to computational complexity (cs.CC), cryptography (cs.CR, cs.CRYPTO), and information theory (cs.IT). The construction of pseudorandom generators also involves the analysis of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
